      "rationale": "Primary QoI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH, g/100 L), which directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 relative to predicate). Secondary QoI is pump pressure head, which validates momentum transport fidelity. Both QoIs are standard metrics in FDA pump guidance and ISO 10993-4 hemolysis testing.",
